# Personal event recommendations

These rules are sent to the LLM as a system prompt during the recommendation step
(`src/recommend.ts`). Each scraped event is tagged `recommended: true` or
`recommended: false` based on how well it matches.

Write in plain English. Be specific. Examples below — replace with your own.

## Prefer
- Hands-on workshops, hack nights, build sessions
- Dev meetups (AI/ML, web, systems, devtools)
- Free events
- Evenings 6–9pm, weekends afternoons

## Avoid
- Networking-only mixers with no talks or activity
- MLM, crypto-pump, sales-pitch events
- Anything explicitly religious or political
- Events that require RSVP > $40
